Male postabdomen (
Figs. 3–10
). Surstylus fused with epandrium at base; cerci fused completely and strongly constricted laterally on apical 1 / 4 in dorsal view, apex claw-shaped in lateral view; pregonite fused with hypandrium basally; postgonite slender and elongate; epiphallus absent; phallus with a plate medially in lateral view.

